      "module_path": "signal_layer_reader",
      "docs": "Local filesystem adapter implementing `usecase::signal::SignalLayerReader`. Provides local I/O behind the usecase-owned orchestration flow: the usecase asks for the active track through the port, obtains the infrastructure-loaded TDDD layer set through the port as domain `LayerId` values, and requests per-layer catalogue bytes from `track/items/<track-id>/<catalogue-file>`, where `catalogue-file` is the configured `tddd.catalogue_file` and defaults to `<layer>-types.json` when omitted. This adapter owns the filesystem-backed `architecture-rules.json` read/validation for layer enumeration, but not per-layer iteration, catalogue SHA-256 calculation, or signals output path construction; those remain in the usecase/infrastructure responsibilities defined by D8.",
      "spec_refs": [
        { "file": "track/items/signal-gate-strictness-config-2026-06-18/spec.json", "anchor": "CN-16" },
